    "description": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When you roll a </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>13 or higher</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">on a Check performed to investigate a creature, item or location — this includes using the </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Study </strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">action during a conflict — you may ask the Game Master up to </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>【</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>SL</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>】 </strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">questions concerning the subject of your investigation. You may ask these questions immediately or save them for later; whenever you ask one of these questions, the Game Master will answer truthfully and you will describe your character's deductive process.</span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This Skill may only be used once on the same creature, item or location.</span> </p>",
